The paper deals with modeling relational data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The use of latent factors and blockmodels suggests that the paper may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The mention of recommender systems and bioinformatics also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of data science (cs.DS) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of optimization transfer algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of optimization and control (cs.OC).
